in classical music , two of the most - famous barcaroles are jacques offenbach 's " belle nuit , ô nuit d'amour " , from his opera the tales of hoffmann ; and frédéric chopin 's barcarole in f - sharp major for solo piano .

classical music : this offenbach work that contains the popular " barcarolle " premiered in 1881 after his death

tales of hoffman